signatureAbility.signatureDescription: The game's top defenders excel in all situations. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance of defeating run blocks, tackling runners, and disrupting catches.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Defenders with this ability don't allow broken tackles when hit-sticking ballcarriers - regardless of the runner's size or power.
Some players thrive on making defenders look silly. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their fakeout rate on the next juke, spin or hurdle.
Ballcarriers with this ability have faster juke and spin animations.
Running backs with this ability have better catch in traffic and route running when coming out of the backfield against linebackers and linemen.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Defenders with this ability use dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
Aggressive receivers overpower defenders and attack the football. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on aggressive catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running in and out routes.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running streak routes.
Players with this ability have an increased chance to catch passes that have been tipped into the air.
Defenders with this ability play tighter coverage and force more catch knockouts in both man-to-man and zone.
Some pass rushers intimidate quarterbacks with their sheer presence. When they enter the zone, they can apply significant pressure on quarterbacks even while engaged with blockers.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Defenders with this ability use dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
Quarterbacks with generational arms have the power to stretch any defense to its breaking point. When they enter the zone, their maximum throw distance is increased by 15+ yards.
Passers with this ability have a higher chance of completing a pass animation (and throwing the ball) while being sacked.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful truck animations.
Midway through the fourth quarter in close games, players with this ability can easily enter (and remain in) the Zone.
